# .private-secret-patterns — local, UNVERSIONED extra rules for scripts/secret-scan.sh
#
# This repo was extracted from private codebases. The committed scanner ships only
# GENERIC rules (token shapes, generic PII/infra shapes). Project-specific PRIVATE
# strings — real client/brand names, signing identities, internal repo/host names,
# private backend symbols — must NOT be committed (publishing them leaks exactly what
# the gate protects). Put them here instead.
#
# Copy this file to `.private-secret-patterns` (gitignored) and replace the example
# values with your real ones. The scanner loads it automatically if present; on a
# public clone it is absent and only the generic rules run.
#
# Format: one rule per line  ->  flag@@@label@@@regex
#   flag:  i = case-insensitive, s = case-sensitive
#   label: short id shown when a match is BLOCKED
#   regex: extended POSIX regex (grep -E)
# Blank lines and lines starting with # are ignored.
#
# ---- examples (FAKE values — replace with your own) ----
# i@@@client:acme@@@acme corp
# s@@@identity:appleteam@@@AB1234CDEF
# s@@@identity:userpath@@@/Users/your-username
# s@@@origin:private-repo@@@your-org/your-private-repo
# i@@@infra:host@@@your-internal-host
# s@@@backend-symbol:authHelper@@@someInternalAuthSymbol
